gomodel:SYNGO_2593  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: GluD2 is localizes to the postsynaptic density membrane of Parallel Fiber (PF)-Purkinje cells synapses in the cerebellum.\n\nSupplementary Fig. S11: Immunogold labeling for GluD2 by SDS-digested freeze-fracture replica labeling in the molecular layer of cerebellar tissue from WT and GluD2-KO mice. \"Immunoparticles for GluD2 (10 nm) accumulated over a postsynaptic membrane specialization...in wild-type (A), but not in GluD2-null (B), mouse cerebellum.\" The number of GluD2 particles at these synapses was positively correlated with the synapse size (E). Double labeling of AMPARs (anti-pan GluA, 5 nm particles) and GluD2 (15 nm particles) in a Sprague-Dawley rat showed a similar distribution of both proteins at PF-PC synapses.\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: From methods section:\nFor SDS-digested freeze-fracture replica labeling (SDS-FRL) of GluD2, cbln1-null or wild-type mice at postnatal 6 to 7 weeks (n = 2 mice for each)....\n\nFrom Supplemental Figure S11:\nDouble labeling using anti-pan GluA (5 nm particles) and anti-GluD2 (15 nm particles) antibodies in a Sprague-Dawley rat (C)...." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2593" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

